Integer Types:

char: 8 bits, Range: -128 to 127 (signed), 0 to 255 (unsigned)

short: 16 bits, Range: -32,768 to 32,767 (signed), 0 to 65,535 (unsigned)

int: 16 or 32 bits (depending on the system), Range: -32,768 to 32,767 (16-bit signed), -2,147,483,648 to 2,147,483,647 (32-bit signed)

long: 32 bits, Range: -2,147,483,648 to 2,147,483,647 (signed), 0 to 4,294,967,295 (unsigned)

long long: 64 bits, Range: -9,223,372,036,854,775,808 to 9,223,372,036,854,775,807 (signed), 0 to 18,446,744,073,709,551,615 (unsigned)

Floating-Point Types:

float: 32 bits, Range: ~1.2E-38 to ~3.4E+38

double: 64 bits, Range: ~2.3E-308 to ~1.7E+308

long double: 80 or 128 bits (depending on the system), Range: ~3.4E-4932 to ~1.1E+4932 (80-bit), ~3.4E-4932 to ~1.1E+4932 (128-bit)

Boolean Type:

bool: 1 bit, Range: 0 (false) or 1 (true)

Pointer Types:

void*: 16, 32, or 64 bits (depending on the system), Range: Addressable memory space

Fixed-Point Types (used in some embedded systems):

Q7: 8 bits, Range: -1.0 to (1.0 - 2^-7)

Q15: 16 bits, Range: -1.0 to (1.0 - 2^-15)

Q31: 32 bits, Range: -1.0 to (1.0 - 2^-31)
